value               package:NeuroImage               R Documentation

_a _f_u_n_c_t_i_o_n _t_o _a_c_c_e_s_s _t_h_e _v_a_l_u_e _g_i_v_e_n _a _r_e_a_l _w_o_r_l_d _c_o_o_r_d_i_n_a_t_e

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     this function takes real world coordinate locations and returns an
     interpolated image value.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     value(object, x, y, ...)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

  object: an object derived from class "BrainData" 

       x: the x real world coordinate 

       y: the y real worold coordinate 

     ...: world coordinates for additional dimensions 

_D_e_t_a_i_l_s:

     coordinates supplied to the function will first be multiplied by
     the inverse transformation matrix associated with the "BrainSpace"
     object, yileding a set of numeric grid positions. An image value
     will be computed via linear interpolation.

_V_a_l_u_e:

     interploated value at real world coordinates.

